3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Paradex calculates funding rates every hour using a premium-weighted approach between the perpetual mark price and IMX spot index. Rates are capped at ±0.75% per funding period to prevent extreme volatility. The exchange's portfolio margin system allows cross-collateral positions, enabling efficient funding rate strategies across multiple gaming tokens. Settlement occurs automatically without requiring manual intervention, with funding payments reflected in your portfolio balance."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","IMX","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"IMX perpetuals on Paradex exhibit higher funding rate volatility due to the gaming token's speculative nature and the DEX's lower liquidity compared to centralized exchanges. The 1-hour funding cycles create more frequent arbitrage windows, particularly during gaming sector narratives or IMX ecosystem developments. Portfolio margin capabilities allow traders to hedge funding exposure across correlated gaming tokens efficiently."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"IMX funding rates on Paradex have shown significant volatility around major gaming industry announcements and metaverse trends. During positive gaming sentiment, rates frequently spike above 0.3% hourly as long positions dominate. The token's correlation with broader gaming sector movements creates predictable funding patterns during NFT marketplace updates or Immutable X partnership announcements. Weekend trading often sees compressed funding rates due to lower retail participation in gaming tokens."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The 1-hour funding cycle creates 24 daily arbitrage opportunities compared to traditional 8-hour cycles on centralized exchanges. Paradex's relatively low liquidity can cause funding rates to deviate significantly from other venues during volatile periods. Cross-margin functionality enables delta-neutral strategies where traders can collect funding payments while hedging spot exposure through other gaming tokens. Early-stage exchange dynamics often result in inefficient funding rate pricing during Asia-Pacific trading hours."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"StarkNet's complexity introduces smart contract risks specific to the L2 infrastructure, particularly during network upgrades or congestion. Limited IMX liquidity on Paradex can result in significant slippage during position adjustments, especially for larger arbitrage sizes. The exchange's early-stage nature means potential platform risks including bugs, governance changes, or liquidity provider exits. Gaming token volatility can trigger unexpected liquidations even in seemingly hedged positions due to correlation breakdowns during market stress."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What makes IMX funding rates different on Paradex compared to centralized exchanges?","answer":"Paradex uses 1-hour funding cycles versus the standard 8-hour cycles on most CEXs, creating more frequent rate adjustments. The DEX structure and lower liquidity often result in higher absolute funding rates and greater volatility around gaming sector events."},{"question":"How does portfolio margin affect IMX funding rate strategies?","answer":"Portfolio margin allows you to use IMX positions as collateral for other gaming token trades, enabling cross-hedged funding strategies. This reduces capital requirements and allows for more complex arbitrage positions across correlated gaming assets."},{"question":"What are the main risks of trading IMX perps on a StarkNet-based DEX?","answer":"Key risks include StarkNet smart contract vulnerabilities, potential L2 network congestion affecting trade execution, and the exchange's early-stage development status. Gaming token correlation breakdowns can also impact hedged positions unexpectedly."},{"question":"When do IMX funding rates typically spike highest on Paradex?","answer":"Rates usually peak during major gaming industry announcements, Immutable X ecosystem updates, or broader metaverse/NFT market rallies. The 1-hour cycles mean these spikes can be captured more frequently than on traditional 8-hour funding exchanges."}]}]
